a study has outlined that 30 percent of australians complain about their lack of sleep on a daily basis . the average adult needs around eight hours of sleep per night with a range of seven to nine . any less than six hours or any more than 10 hours is unusual for the standard person . professor david hillman said the eight hours per night does not necessarily need to be consecutive .
