scientists at the new jersey institute of technology has revealed the first high-resolution footage of a solar flux ` rope ' taking shape on the sun . the new footage was revealed in a paper in nature communications led by dr haimin wang . they are essentially twisted bundles of magnetic field that extend out of and back into the surface across hundreds of kilometres . the formation of a flux rope can take weeks , but the moment when it is flung into the atmosphere can take just a matter of hours .
