fossils from an extinct pygmy sperm whale that died seven million years ago have shed new light on the evolution of modern day whales . the remains , which were discovered in panama , indicate that the organ involved in sound generation and echolocation got smaller throughout the whale 's evolution . although many whales , dolphins and porpoises have a long fossil record , enabling scientists to understand their evolution .
the spooky experiment conjured up a ghostly illusion in the laboratory has proved once and for all that it 's only our mind playing tricks . the invisible , creepy presence reported by so many people over the centuries is just a set of mixed-up signals in the brain . when conducted in real time , the participant 's brain could adapt and recognize it as their own movement because of the synchronized movement .
