archaeologists studied stone tools used by people in the early ahmarian culture , living in south and west europe and west asia around 40,000 years ago . they found the human tools were no more effective than neanderthal-created tools of the same era . the discovery means we may need to rethink the reasons humans survived neanderthals - and that we may not have behaved as differently as we thought .
