the great dying , which struck the earth 252 million years ago , wiped out more than 96 % of the world 's creatures . while extreme volcanic eruptions are commonly blamed for triggering the event , research has found the majority of species on the planet were ultimately killed when the oceans became more acidic . the study , led by the university of edinburgh , is the first to show that highly acidic oceans were to blame .
