scientists have found vast deep water gas hydrates in the arctic that are reservoirs for abiotic methane -- a gas which is 20 times more effective in trapping heat than carbon dioxide . serpentinisation occurs when seawater reacts with hot mantle rocks exhumed along large faults within the seafloor . instead , they say similar formations could someday be used to store methane , that can later be used as fuel .
