brain scans on a group of professional comedians has revealed differences in the way the brains of these ` super speakers ' work while talking . compared to the less silver tongued among us , the super speakers showed less activity in a key area of the brain involved articulating and comprehending speech . this suggests that this group were putting less effort into the basic mechanics of speech , allowing them to devote more resources to what they were going to say next .
